    <div class="group row" >
      <h3>What is safeguard</h3>
      <p>Safeguard has been set up to cover expected losses. Our loss expectations are based on our historical loan performance, and assume a similar economic enviroment. It is not a guarantee. <a href="/lending/risk-data#safeguard">Find out more about safeguard.</a></p>
      <p>For products that don't have safeguard, whilst expected returns are higher so is the anticipated credit risk. <a href="/lending/risk-markets">Find out more risk markets.</a></p>
      <h3>Getting your money out</h3>
      <p>In all our products, you can withdraw your money for free as borrowers repay. To do this you can choose to switch auto-lending off. Borrowers may pay back loans early, and often do.</p>
      <p>If you choose to sell your loans to withdraw all, or a lump sum, there needs to be other lenders to buy your loans. To date, this has always been possible but it is not a guarantee. If you sell your loans to another lender, a premium may be charged if your loans are worth less than the open market (for example, if rates for loans have increased). <a href="/lending/access-your-money">Find out more about accessing your money.</a></p>
    </div>
